---
By: Lyman Abbott
Locus:
  Page: 82
  Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Death
---
c Death is only pushing aside the portiere and passing from one room to
another. ...I think of death as a glad awakening from this troubled sleep
which we call life; as an emancipation from the world which, beautiful
though it be, is still a land of captivity.
